      "side": 1,
      "message": "Just to clarify my idea: https://skia.googlesource.com/skcms/+/refs/heads/master/tests.c#712\n\nThat function is part of the skcms unit test suite. It goes through a hard-coded list of .icc files (though we could also just do *all* files in some directory...). For each one it parses and dumps out the parse results to a text buffer. \u0027regen\u0027 is tied to a command line flag. If that\u0027s true, we just write out the buffer to a corresponding .txt file, otherwise we read the .txt file and diff against the buffer, printing out any mismatches and failing the test.",
